{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nrebar has no general mechanism to apply an idempotent setup/config change to an\nALREADY-EXISTING install. Init-time `_migrate_*`/`_ensure_*` functions (e.g.\n`_migrate_gc_config`) run only at `init`/re-init, so a fix shipped after a store was\ninitialized never reaches it unless someone re-inits — the gap the `gc.auto=0` legacy-store\nissue exposed. Discovered from the gc discussion (e3d0).\n\n**School B (desired-state / convergent), not School A (ordered ledger).** Idempotent,\nsafe-to-re-run, drift-correcting (Ansible/Puppet/Chef check-then-act `changed`/`ok`; K8s\nlevel-triggered reconcile). We do NOT build an ordered version ledger (Alembic/Flyway/Rails\nare for irreversible, unsafe-to-rerun migrations). The A-tier ledger (committed store-format\nversion, ordered, fail-closed on too-new) is future work (docs/migrations.md + doctor idea dabb).\n\n## Design (corrected against origin/main via two plan-review passes)\n**Ensure-registry (`ensures.py`).** A registry of ensure units, each `{stable, immutable id,\ncallable(tracker) -> EnsureOutcome}` where the callable is check-then-act (no-op when\nconverged) and `EnsureOutcome` is a small dataclass `{id, status: Literal[\"ok\",\"changed\",\n\"failed\"], detail}`. `run_ensures(tracker)` runs ALL units unconditionally under the STORE\nwrite lock (`_store/lock.py` write_lock — init_core does NOT currently hold it), catches a\nraising unit (skip-and-continue → `failed`), returns the outcome list, and rewrites\n`.ensure-applied` to the ids of the NON-failed (ok/changed) units only.\n\n**The exact 5 re-init idempotent steps migrated** (init.py:209-213 — the already-initialized\npath that reaches existing stores): `env-id`, `gc-config`, `merge-ours driver`,\n`gitattributes` (COMMIT), `gitignore` (COMMIT). **Two units commit** (gitattributes AND\ngitignore) → check-then-act (tree-check before commit) required for BOTH. These same units\nalso appear on the fresh-init path (init.py:242-248) and `_ensure_env_id` is additionally\ncalled from `_init_via_symlink` (init.py:564, 582); the migration wires `run_ensures()` at all\ninit entry points and removes the hand-listed calls from each, with no double-execution. The\nfresh-init-only bootstrap (`_commit_precommit`, `_gen_local_files`, `_exclude_scratch_in_tracker`,\n`_ensure_branch_user_config`) are NOT ensures and stay.\n\n**Entry points (non-hot):** init/re-init/symlink-init (always), `rebar fsck --repair` (opt-in),\nMCP server startup (best-effort — log-and-continue, never abort boot; under write lock). The\nsweep never runs on the hot write path or on pure reads.\n\n**fsck reconciliation (origin/main ALREADY has `fsck --repair`).** `fsck --repair` is the\nexisting A3 data-remediation verb (rebuild snapshots, retire orphans; requires mutation;\n`--dry-run`/`--limit`). We do NOT add a new `--fix` flag — we FOLD the ensure-sweep into the\nexisting `--repair` path (one \"drive to healthy\" verb, both data + config). Plain read-only\n`rebar fsck` gains an `ensures: N/M applied` line derived WITHOUT calling run_ensures: M =\ncount of registry ids, N = count present in `.ensure-applied`. The pending-hint points to\n`rebar fsck --repair`.\n\n**Concurrency.** run_ensures runs under the store write lock so concurrent sweeps serialize;\ncheck-then-act makes the second sweep a no-op. gitattributes/gitignore use `merge=ours`.\n`.ensure-applied` is a full atomic rewrite (temp+rename) of the current non-failed id set — no\nread-modify-write.\n\n**Applied-set marker + write-path pending-hint (Rails CheckPending, hardened).**\n- `.ensure-applied` (WS1-owned: format+write) and `.ensure-hinted` (WS2-owned) — both git-ignored\n  (ADD BOTH to `_GITIGNORE`, init.py:38-48), atomic; `.ensure-applied` = JSON array, absent/garbage\n  → empty set; `.ensure-hinted` = last-hinted timestamp.\n- Hook the COMMON mutation paths via `_seam.append_event` / `event_append.write_and_push`\n  (create/edit/link/comment/tag/set_*/sign/transition/claim), lazy import. Best-effort, NOT\n  universal: `compact.py`, `txn.py`/`transition_close.py`, `delete.py` commit inline and are\n  intentionally NOT hooked (acceptable — a rate-limited nudge, not correctness).\n- `pending = registry ids − parsed .ensure-applied`, computed ONCE per process (cached boolean;\n  registry static in a process). Converged store adds ≤1 read/process; reads untouched.\n- Emit a WARNING → `rebar fsck --repair` only when pending AND `.ensure-hinted` older than the\n  interval; then atomically update it. Interval + suppression are typed config (`EnsureConfig`\n  in `_config_schema.py`: `ensure.hint_interval_secs`=86400, `ensure.hint_enabled`=true), with a\n  section-derived env override — note: the AST drift gate (`gen_env_registry. No manual edits to generated docs.\n- Hook swallows ALL its own exceptions incl. lazy-import ImportError/SyntaxError (debug log) — a\n  write NEVER fails on the nag. Rare double-hint under concurrency accepted.\n- Marker gates the HINT ONLY, never the repair. Fresh auto-init'd worktree converges at init → never hints.\n\n**Accepted trade-offs:** long-lived MCP server converges at boot, does not re-sweep mid-life\n(drift caught at next `fsck --repair`) — WS4 documents it; a permanently-failing unit stays out\nof the set and is named in the rate-limited hint. Post-rollback: old code simply ignores the\ngit-ignored `.ensure-applied`/`.ensure-hinted` files (no schema coupling).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ensures.py` registry generalizes the 5 re-init units; each is check-then-act with a stable/immutable id + `EnsureOutcome` result; BOTH commit units (gitattributes, gitignore) tree-check (second run → zero commits)\n- [ ] `run_ensures()` runs unconditionally under the store write lock at all init entry points, `fsck --repair`, and MCP startup (best-effort at startup); NEVER gated on the marker\n- [ ] Migration removes the hand-listed calls from BOTH re-init and fresh-init paths (and handles `_ensure_env_id`'s `_init_via_symlink` callers) with no double-execution\n- [ ] The ensure-sweep is folded into the EXISTING `fsck --repair` (no new flag); plain `fsck` prints `ensures: N/M applied` read-only (M=registry ids, N=in `.ensure-applied`, without calling run_ensures)\n- [ ] `fsck --repair` heals and is git-level idempotent (twice → zero new commits); the pending-hint points to `rebar fsck --repair`\n- [ ] Best-effort write-path pending-hint on the common mutation paths (inline committers acknowledged out); pure reads untouched; ≤1 read/process; never fails a write (incl. lazy-import errors)\n- [ ] Hint rate-limited via `.ensure-hinted` + typed-config interval (86400s) + section-derived env suppression (documented in docs/env-vars.md); fresh auto-init'd worktree never hints\n- [ ] `.ensure-applied` (JSON array, atomic full rewrite of non-failed ids) + `.ensure-hinted` are added to `_GITIGNORE`; absent/garbage → empty set (no crash)\n- [ ] `run_ensures()` has a typed `EnsureOutcome` + partial-failure contract (skip-and-continue; init logs failures, never aborts)\n- [ ] Hot-path regression test: mutation ops may hint but never invoke `run_ensures` (no git-config subprocess; ≤1 marker read/process)\n- [ ] `docs/migrations.md` documents reuse, marker-gates-hint-never-repair, hot-path contract, long-lived-MCP trade-off, post-rollback file-ignore, and A-tier future; gc-config is the reference unit"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783581515654218001,"uuid":"86eb44c8-b32c-4869-97f6-7ee87d8caf5f"}